  "original_title": "\u0d85\u0db4\u0dd2\u0da7 \u0da7\u0dd2\u0dc0\u0dd2\u0da7\u0dbb\u0dca \u0db4\u0dab\u0dd2\u0dc0\u0dd2\u0da9 \u0db1\u0dd1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "We don't have Twitter messages",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Former minister Mr. Wimalaweera Dissanayake said that it is regrettable to point out that when the houses of seventy-two MPs were set on fire, neither the lawyers' organization nor humanitarian organizations nor ambassadors issued any Twitter messages against that crime.",
        "Gotabaya Rajapaksa, who came to power with a mandate of 69 lakhs, and Mahinda Rajapaksa, who came to the post of Prime Minister with almost two-thirds of the power, had hoped that the country would be prosperous by sending them home. The MP also mentioned that it should have started.",
        "He said that many councilors fell on the streets due to the burning of houses and that he was also a person who fell on the streets.",
        "Mr. Wimalaweera Dissanayake said that he has a problem with the struggles of those who wear earrings and grow beards and said that everyone with common sense knows very well where these people are trying to take this country."
      ],
